        {
            "_id": "TFDyM40f7so2E11B",
            "img": "systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/action.svg",
            "name": "Serenity Vulnerability",
            "sort": 1000000,
            "system": {
                "actionType": {
                    "value": "passive"
                },
                "actions": {
                    "value": null
                },
                "category": "offensive",
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p>A demonic rabble thrives on mayhem, and when members of the throng find themselves facing moments of calm, however brief or temporary, the throng suffers. Whenever the demonic rabble fails a saving throw against an affect that would normally @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Fascinated]{Fascinate}, @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Fatigued]{Fatigue}, @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Paralyzed]{Paralyze}, @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Restrained]{Restrain}, or @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Slowed]{Slow} at least four creatures, the troop takes [[/r 3d6[mental]]] damage.</p>"
                },
                "requirements": {
                    "value": ""
